The paper focuses on the application of deep learning to EEG analysis, which falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of DL in EEG analysis also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it aims to improve the interpretation of EEG signals for various applications. Additionally, the paper discusses the reproducibility of experiments, which is a topic relevant to the field of cybernetics (cs.CY).
